There are 4 different nationalities: colombian, indian, japanese, russian
The people use 4 different means of transport: car, subway, snowmobile, airplane
 1. the colombian is somewhere to the left of the person driving the subway##5
 2. the person drinking tea is on the right of the person drinking coffee##1
 3. the person driving the airplane is on the far left or far right##3
 4. the person driving the snowmobile is between the indian and the japanese##2
 5. the person driving the car is somewhere to the right of the russian##5
 6. the person drinking coffee is somewhere to the left of the person drinking hot-chocolate##5
 7. the indian is not the person drinking tea##6
 8. the person driving the car is somewhere between the person drinking hot-chocolate and the person drinking water##7
 9. the colombian is somewhere to the left of the japanese##5
10. the person driving the airplane is on the left of the person driving the car##1
11. the colombian is between the japanese and the indian##2

.:: Answer ::.
|               |    1     |     2      |     3      |    4     |
| Beverage      | water | coffee     | tea      | hot-chocolate     |
| Nationality   | russian  | indian   | colombian   | japanese |
| Transport     | airplane     | car | snowmobile | subway   |

